text: "During a summer wedding reception, 150 guests were served a buffet meal that included chicken salad, seafood pasta, and fruit desserts. Within 8\u201312 hours, dozens of guests begin experiencing sudden-onset abdominal cramps, nausea, vomiting, and diarrhea. By the next morning, nearly all affected guests had symptoms, but no new cases occurred after 24\u201336 hours.<br><br>An epidemiologic investigation reveals that illness was strongly associated with eating the chicken salad, which was later found to have been contaminated with Staphylococcus aureus enterotoxin.<br><br>Which of the following best describes the epidemic pattern of this outbreak?",
options: [{"id": "A", "text": "Point source single exposure epidemic", "is_correct": true}, {"id": "B", "text": "Continuous common source epidemic", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "C", "text": "Propagated epidemic", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "D", "text": "Mixed epidemic", "is_correct": false}],
explanation: "Key features of the outbreak:<br><br>* **Single event** (wedding reception)\n* **Common exposure** (chicken salad contaminated with *Staphylococcus aureus* enterotoxin)\n* **Short incubation period** (8\u201312 hours \u2192 preformed toxin)\n* **Sudden surge of cases**, followed by **rapid decline**\n* **No secondary cases** after 24\u201336 hours<br><br>These are classic characteristics of a **point source (single exposure) epidemic**.",
images: []
