text: "Researchers are studying the prevalence of intravenous drug use in a large metropolitan area. Because this is a stigmatized and hard-to-reach population, investigators initially identify a small group of participants through community outreach programs. Each participant is then asked to refer friends or acquaintances who also use intravenous drugs, and those referrals are further asked to recruit others. The sample gradually expands until the desired sample size is reached.<br><br>Which of the following best describes the sampling strategy used in this study?",
options: [{"id": "A", "text": "Simple random sampling", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "B", "text": "Stratified random sampling", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "C", "text": "Cluster sampling", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "D", "text": "Snowball sampling", "is_correct": true}],
explanation: "The study involves:<br><br>* A **hard-to-reach / stigmatized population** (intravenous drug users)\n* **Initial participants identified through outreach**\n* **Participants recruiting others from their social networks**\n* Progressive expansion of the sample until the target size is achieved<br><br>These are the defining features of **Snowball sampling**.<br><br>###### Why Snowball sampling fits:<br><br>\n* A **non-probability sampling method**\n* Especially useful for **hidden, marginalized, or stigmatized populations**\n    (e.g., IV drug users, sex workers, MSM)\n* Recruitment proceeds **chain-referral style**",
