explanation: "The described approach selects sampling units in **stages**. First, villages are selected as primary sampling units. Next, households are selected within the chosen villages as secondary sampling units. This is the classic definition of **multistage sampling**, commonly used in community prevalence surveys because it is logistically feasible when a complete list of all households in the district is not easily available.",
