explanation: "**Lead time** is the interval between **detection of disease by screening** and **usual clinical diagnosis**. Excessive lead time can distort survival statistics (**lead time bias**).\n**How to minimize lead time in screening programs:**<br><br>* **Periodic (regular) screening** ensures cases are detected **closer to the time they would become clinically apparent**, rather than too early.\n* This **reduces artificial inflation of survival time** without truly improving prognosis.",
