text: "Which of the following statements is NOT true regarding random errors in epidemiological studies?",
options: [{"id": "A", "text": "Sampling errors are examples of random errors", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "B", "text": "Random errors can cause bias in a study", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "C", "text": "Random errors cannot be completely eliminated", "is_correct": true}, {"id": "D", "text": "Systematic errors are different from random errors", "is_correct": false}],
explanation: "**Random error** refers to **chance variation** in measurements or sampling. It affects **precision**, not validity.<br><br>* **Bias = systematic error**, not random error\n* Random error causes **imprecision** (results fluctuate around the true value)\n* It does **not consistently push results in one direction**, so it does **not cause bias**",
