explanation: "Annual growth rate (natural increase) is calculated as:<br><br>Growth rate = CBR \u2212 CDR<br><br>Given:<br><br>CBR = 19 per 1000<br><br>CDR = 6 per 1000<br><br>Natural increase = 19 \u2212 6 = 13 per 1000 population\nSo,\nAnnual growth rate = 13 / 1000 = 1.3% per year",
