tags: ["Formulae_Numbers"],
text: "Based on the graphical representation provided, which of the following equations corresponds to the regression model of the plotted graph?",
options: [{"id": "A", "text": "y=10-\u0445", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "B", "text": "x=10+\u0443", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "C", "text": "y=11+2x", "is_correct": true}, {"id": "D", "text": "x=11+2y", "is_correct": false}],
explanation: "The graph shows a straight-line relationship with a positive slope of 2 and a Y-intercept of 11. Therefore, the Linear regression equation is y = 11 + 2x, which correctly represents the plotted data. <br><br>REGRESSION formulae:<br><br>* y=a+bx \u2013 Simple linear regression \n* y=a+b\\_1 x\\_1+b\\_2 x\\_2+\u22ef+b\\_n x\\_n \u2013 Multiple linear regression \n* y=a+bx+cx2 \u2013 Curvilinear regression",
