explanation: "The recommended dietary allowance (RDA) for calcium in pregnancy is 1000 mg/day, while in lactation it increases to 1200 mg/day to compensate for calcium loss in breast milk. Adequate calcium intake is essential for maternal bone health and fetal skeletal development.<br><br><img src=\"https://corebtr-assets-production.s3.ap-south-1.amazonaws.com/question_explanation/2604dc9f-83f8-42ba-ba88-1b290b8fef6e.png\" alt=\"Uploaded Image\">",
