text: "Which international initiative focuses on providing vaccines to children in developing countries to prevent diseases such as measles, polio, and tetanus?",
options: [{"id": "A", "text": "World Bank Group", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "B", "text": "Doctors Without Borders", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "C", "text": "Global Fund", "is_correct": false}, {"id": "D", "text": "GAVI", "is_correct": true}],
explanation: "Gavi, the Vaccine Alliance is a global public\u2013private partnership dedicated to improving access to immunization in low- and middle-income countries, targeting diseases like measles, polio, tetanus, hepatitis B, and others.<br><br>World Bank Group focuses on development financing and policy support.<br><br>Doctors Without Borders (MSF) provides emergency medical aid, not a global vaccine-financing initiative.<br><br>Global Fund primarily addresses HIV/AIDS, tuberculosis, and malaria, not routine childhood immunization.",
